cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC 

This paper deals with computational complexity and algorithms for manipulating the Borda voting rule, which is a topic in computational social choice. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also proposes approximation methods based on bin packing and multiprocessor scheduling, which are topics in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DM). The use of approximation algorithms also suggests the category cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper uses ideas from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to propose and evaluate the approximation methods.
